						<summary>

						<p>This is an incomplete record. It mentions <hi rend="bold">Bakuḷam</hi> evidently a village in [Kāṉa]ppēr-kūṟṟam in Pāṇḍi-nāḍu. The subdivision occurs in the <hi rend="italic">Bigger Śinnamanūr Plates</hi> as Tirukkānappēr-kūṟṟam (<hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> III 4. p. 462). <hi rend="bold">The alphabet is early</hi> and the the record may be one of <hi rend="bold">Āditya I.</hi></p>						

